Use the standard library
This is how to even_odd_palindrome of n:
  Remember that evens is 0
  Remember that odds is 0
  Remember that i is 1
  Do this n times:
    Remember that s is tostring of i
    Remember that r is ""
    Remember that j is diff of s's length and 1
    Do this s's length times:
      Remember that r is "{r}{item j in s}"
      Decrease j by 1
    End do
    Remember that even_pal is toint of "{s}{r}"
    Remember that odd_pal is toint of "{s}{item diff of s's length and 1 in r}"
    Increase evens by 1
    When odd_pal is at most n, then:
      Increase odds by 1
    End when
    Increase i by 1
    When even_pal is more than n, then:
      Leave the loop
    End when
  End do
  The answer is [evens, odds]
Now you know